-- Capital One quarterly profit falls on higher loan loss provision
-- By Avik Das in Bangalore
-- Thu Oct 16, 2014 04:22PM EDT
-- None



Oct 16 (Reuters) - Capital One Financial Corp <COF.N> reported a 2.9 percent fall in quarterly profit as it set aside more money to cover soured loans.

The company's net income attributable to shareholders fell to $1.06 billion, or $1.86 per share, for the third quarter ended Sept. 30, from $1.09 billion, or $1.84 per share, a year earlier. [ID:nPn6vGK3] Capital One raised its provision for credit losses by 17 percent to $993 million, from a year earlier.